commit.message:
added saveQuickTune and reuseQuickTune args to setFrequency

This allows to save the bladerf_quick_tune (with args["saveQuickTune"]="1") when setting a specific frequency, and then reusing that bladerf_quick_tune when going back to that frequency (with args["reuseQuickTune"]="1").

It's also possible to schedule the frequency retune when reusing a bladerf_quick_tune by setting args["timestamp"] to the string representation of the desired timestamp.

commit.message:
implement deprecated listsamplerates and bandwidths

The ranges api for sample rates returns 3 ranges based on bladerf
results. The listsamplerates then iterates through to get a discrete
list. The listbandwidths just use the old discrete list for v1.

Fixed hasGainMode to probe automatic mode

It's fairly bulletproof now - attempts to set automatic mode, and if it fails,
returns false.

Implemented a more accurate hasGainMode

Presence/absence of LUT for AGC makes it actually a bit tough to tell whether or
not setGainMode will work, or error out as unsupported. This commit changes it
to check by attempting to set the gain mode, and then return true or false based
on the actual behavior. This way, hasGainMode is truly an indicator of whether
or not setGainMode is supported or not.
